  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is an open, prospective, single-site study where 16 patients suffering from fecal
      incontinence will be included. Change in fecal incontinence episodes after intersphincteric
      injection of NASHA/Dx gel 4x2 ml and retreatment 4x2 ml after 4 weeks will be measured.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
